<td><font class="pn-title"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=5">N.A.T.O. News</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=45&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">Jemand Verbieten returns to N.A.T.O.</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal">Former <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="N.A.T.O." target="_blank">N.A.T.O.</a> guild, Jemand Verbieten, has formally requested to once again become an active member in the Norrath Alliance Treaty Organization (N.A.T.O.).  Norinth, the new leader of JV, has spent the last several weeks getting the swing of things and discussing with his Officers wether or not JV should resume relations with the Alliance or remain unallied with any guilds at all.  Earlier today, he met again with <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/~xorrin/" title="Xorrin Aarikis" target="_blank">Xorrin</a> Aarikis to close any loose issues, and make it clear that JV was once again an active guild on Vazaelle, and that his members all agree that being a member of N.A.T.O. was a positive experience for them.  In a recent vote, they decided to once again pursue membership in N.A.T.O., and look forward to once again grouping and raiding with their old friends.</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Sep 21, 2003 - 05:15 AM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
