<td><font class="pn-title"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=1">Raid Announcements</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=44&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">Maelloni's Epic and Monday Night Raid</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal">Hail All,<br />
  Yesterday, August 31, TaO along with several N.A.T.O Guild members hit and easily destroyed Fay in TD for Sister Maelloni's last epic peice.<br />
  There were members from several guilds including RBD.<br />
  Even some old <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="N.A.T.O." target="_blank">N.A.T.O.</a> allies helped.  Everyone followed commands as they were given and things went very smoothly.<br />
  Congrats everyone on a job well done!<br />
************************************************<br />
  TaO will be raiding this evening between 4 and 5pm pacific time.  We are scheduled to hit Plane of Fear or Chardok depending on availability.<br />
  Anyone interested in coming should meet at the OverThere Stone in PoK sometime around 4pm pacific.<br />
  Monday raids are for Epic Hits so we will do what we can to get at least 1 epic piece per raid.<br />
<br />
  Chardok Raid Epic Hit Goal Sept. 1, 2003<br />
Iksar Betrayer - Monk Epic Piece<br />
Prince Selrach Di'zok - Enchanter Epic (1st one going to Chante)<br />
<br />
  Additional:<br />
  If we have the power and time as a unit we will move on to try Queen. This usually takes another hour or so to get too and do so we will decide after taking on Prince.<br />
<br />
  Plane of Fear Raid Epic Hit Goal Sept. 1, 2003<br />
  Golems (minimum) - Wizard, Shaman, Warrior<br />
<br />
  Additional:<br />
  We will go as long as we can in Fear depending on turnout and time.<br />
<br />
  Please do your best to be around from 4pm pacific on as we want to get started asap. Thanks and be well.<br />
<br />
Kimbaa<br />
GM of Together as One</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Sep 01, 2003 - 04:27 PM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
