<tr>
<td><font class="pn-title"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=1">Raid Announcements</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=41&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">Raid On KC, Friday 25 July, 8pm EST</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal"><P ALIGN="justify">All those looking to organize a raid it has been a while. We will be taking down KC. Better Pack a lunch this one could be an all nighter. Plan on Dropping both Warlord's several times, the hands will die, all curates and callers will remain dead, We will even take out Venril Sathir for his class specific greaves that drop a different class everytime. We will focus on the main level but may go to the Catacombs to where is said to be the hardest dungeon in Norrath. KC Also contains components for the Druid, Bard and Wizard Epics, so send me (<A HREF="http://www.vazaelle.net/modules.php?op=modload&name=Messages&file=replypmsg&send=1&uname=Gindorf" TARGET="_top">Gindorf</A>) a private message for accountability and we'll see you there. Start time 8PM EST, Go early to lvl up. All lvls above 37 welcome, everyone gets EXP all the way to LVL 65!</P></font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Jul 22, 2003 - 10:24 PM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr>
<td><font class="pn-title"><a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=40&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">The Naming of a Server</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal">There are many servers from which to choose from when creating your characters in <a href="http://www.EverQuest.com/" title="EverQuest™" target="_blank">EverQuest</a>.  Each server has its own name.  For the most part, the Gods prevail when naming a server.  But what about the others?  Everyone knows who Antonius Bayle, Tunare, and my personal favorite, Cazic-Thule are.  But where do we derive our name from?  Thanks to a new site, <A HREF="http://www.everquestplatinum.com/" TARGET="_new">EverQuest Platinum</A>, we now know that answer!<br />
<br />
</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Note: <i>Considering our members here on Vazaelle.NET, I'd say we all found the right server!  Funny life works sometimes, huh?  ;)<br />
<br />
 - X</i></font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Jun 20, 2003 - 06:51 AM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr>
<td><font class="pn-title"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=3">Site Updates</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=39&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">[20-April-2003&#032;&#064;&#032;20:00 SYD]</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal">Sorry about the loooong delay in getting everything back online.  The site really was done within 2 hours of putting up that temporary &quot;maintenance&quot; page.  The problem came when my computer died.  Power supply, motherboard, even the case!  As a result, I lost all data on BOTH my hard drives...  I just got the system somewhat up and running today, although it's still randomly crashing and rebooting itself for no aparent reason..../rude Micro$oft.<br />
<br />
Anyway, the site is here.  I have the Calendar block, as well as the Gallery (for some reason that one did not port over.  I am going to try a different calendar - CalZone was nice, but I think the administration and customization of this new one will be nicer.<br />
<br />
Finally, the message boards are up and running.  The problem with them lies in that version 2 uses a totally different database than the old version 1.4beta that we were using before.  Everything works now that did not before, but the old forums and messages are still in the old database, waiting for me to figure out how to port them over.  The table structures are completely different, also, so a simple (? over 5,000 messages!) cut &amp; paste is out of the question.  There should be a converter/import script out there somewhere - I just haven't found it yet. ;)<br />
<br />
Oh, one other thing on the forums...  The first time you visit them, you will be &quot;registered&quot; in them.  I hacked the core of the user script on the site to do this automatically, so all your information will be the same.  The only thing you might have to do is re-type your auto-signature file, which is now done from your Preferences in the forum itself, not the My Account link to the main site.<br />
<br />
Once that is done, please send me a private message on the site and let me know which guild you are in and what your rank in that guild is.  I hope to have this step automated for new members in the near future, but for now, I'll just do it manually.  This is important, because the forums security features are now working, as promised!<br />
<br />
That's about it for now.  Still lots of work to be done.  Since I still can't seem to get into <a href="http://www.EverQuest.com/" title="EverQuest™" target="_blank">EQ</a> for more than 5 or 10 minutes at a time without crashing, I'll focus on the site for a while.  Please shoot me your bug reports, suggestions, etc, also.  Thanks!<br />
<br />
 -X</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Apr 20, 2003 - 05:11 AM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr>
<td><font class="pn-title"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=5">N.A.T.O. News</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=38&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">Leaving D'Haran Empire</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal">I regretfully must leave the D'Haran Empire guild.When i took over as GL i discovered it was a sinking ship which i could not recover.Membership dwindled and very few played on a regular basis.It is in my and the few other members interest to move on to a better guild.</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Apr 04, 2003 - 05:07 AM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
<p>
<table width="95%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr>
<td><font class="pn-title"><a href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=index&amp;catid=3">Site Updates</a>: <a class="pn-title" href="modules.php?op=modload&amp;name=News&amp;file=article&amp;sid=37&amp;mode=thread&amp;order=0&amp;thold=0">NEW!  Vazaelle.NET version 7.2.3</a></font><br>
<font class="pn-normal">Beginning today and lasting (hopfully only) over the next 3 days, I will be implimenting the next generation of Vazaelle.NET.<br />
<br />
<B>This is a TOTAL OVERHAUL of the site.  EVERYTHING will be new.</B><br />
<br />
The software will be the same, but is a total rewrite of the currently installed version.  The message boards will finally be updated to a Release version (as opposed to a pre-alpha like the current ones).  I will also be upgrading PHP and MySQL on the server, as well as installing some patches to Linux.<br />
<br />
Although I am doing this from over 30,000 miles of where the server is physically located, I really do not expect any problems to occur.  I either already have, or are in the process of backing up the entire server on my local computer, just in case, and also have a backup job in at the host.<br />
<br />
I am taking every measure to ensure that no data, especially user data, is lost.  After reviewing the code and database structures of the new version of the site, I do not anticipate any data compatibility issues to arise.  Same for the message boards.  With luck, the site itself will be back up and running after being offline for about 20 minutes (time to upload and run install scripts).  While that is happening, I will have a temporary page up.<br />
<br />
Also with this new update, the <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="Knights of the Green Mist" target="_blank">KGM</a> and <a href="http://www.vazaelle.net/" title="N.A.T.O." target="_blank">NATO</a> sites will no longer be found at this URL.  I will post the new URLs when the site is back online, but I think you'll figure it out.  ;)</font><br>
<font class="pn-sub">Published Mar 27, 2003 - 08:47 PM</font>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</p>
